\q1 And terror \add shall issue\add* out of the secret chambers; 
\q1 The young man shall perish with the virgin, 
\q1 The suckling with him who has grown old. 
\q1
\v 26 I said, I will scatter them, 
\q1 And I will cause their memorial to cease from among men. 
\q1
\v 27 Were it not for the wrath of the enemy, lest they should live long, 
\q1 Lest their enemies should combine against them; 
\q1 Lest they should say, Our own high arm, 
\q1 And not the Lord, has done all these things. 
\b
\q1
\v 28 It is a nation that has lost counsel, 
\q1 Neither is there understanding in them. 
\q1
\v 29 They had not sense to understand: 
\q1 Let them reserve these things against the time to come. 
\q1
\v 30 How should one pursue a thousand, 
\q1 And two rout tens of thousands, 
\q1 If God had not sold them, 
\q1 And the Lord delivered them up? 
\q1
\v 31 For their gods are not as our God, 
\q1 But our enemies \add are\add* void of understanding. 
\q1
