\q1 Whensoever their foot shall be tripped up; 
\q1 For the day of their destruction \add is\add* near to them, 
\q1 And the judgments at hand are close upon you. 
\q1
\v 36 For the Lord shall judge his people, 
\q1 And shall be comforted over his servants; 
\q1 For he saw that they were utterly weakened, 
\q1 And failed in the hostile invasion, and were become feeble: 
\q1
